{"title":"Tout Terrain Introduces Divide eMTB with Pinion Motor.Gearbox.Unit","link":"https://bikerumor.com/tout-terrain-divide-emtb-pinion-motor-gearbox-unit/","date":1725654514000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-5482-Large-jpeg.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" /></p>\n<p>Tout Terrain is working on a new bike with a Pinion Gearbox, only this one also has a motor. Named after the Great Divide MTB Route, the Divide e-MTB is a European-made aluminum frame that houses the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pinion-mission-on-e-edrive-is-a-true-ebike-transmission-motor-gearbox-in-one/\" target=\"_blank\">Pinion Motor.Gearbox.Unit (MGU)</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3472-Large-jpeg.webp\"><img width=\"853\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3472-Large-jpeg.webp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3472-Large-jpeg.webp 853w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3472-Large-200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3472-Large-80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3472-Large-768x1152.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-5838-Large-jpeg.webp\"><img width=\"853\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-5838-Large-jpeg.webp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-5838-Large-jpeg.webp 853w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-5838-Large-200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-5838-Large-80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-5838-Large-768x1152.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-jpeg.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-jpeg.webp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/240510_JJANK_ToutTerrain_KarwendelShoot-3451-Large-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Specifically, the frame features the Pinion E1.12 MGU with a Gates Carbon Belt Drive. That gives the bike 12 speeds housed in the gearbox which are shifted with the Pinion Smart.Shift electronic shifting system for a 600% range. The motor will provide assist up to 25 km/h.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-side-web-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"911\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-side-web-1536x911.webp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-side-web-1536x911.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-side-web-297x176.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-side-web-120x71.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-side-web-768x455.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-side-web-2048x1214.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Given that the bike is currently available for pre-order with bikes not expected to ship until Q2 of 2025, details on the frame and battery are still light. We know that the aluminum frame is designed around a 120mm RockShox Pike suspension fork, and it will ride on 29″ wheels and tires (tire clearance and tire size TBA).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Tout-Terrain-Divide-geometry.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1076\" height=\"497\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Tout-Terrain-Divide-geometry.png\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Tout-Terrain-Divide-geometry.png 1076w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Tout-Terrain-Divide-geometry-297x137.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Tout-Terrain-Divide-geometry-120x55.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Tout-Terrain-Divide-geometry-768x355.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Currently, there is only one pre-configured model to pre-order, the Divide Select 5.1 for €7,799. It will be offered in three sizes with short reach numbers compared to most current mountain bikes (the large tops out at 456mm). With stack numbers starting at 648mm for the Small, this will be a fairly upright and comfortable ride for longer days and comfortable exploring. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-1536x1024.webp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-front-1-web-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-1536x1024.webp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/TT_Divide-rear-web-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Divide features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Category: E-X.Over</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Terrain: off-road, trails, gravel</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Aluminum frame made in Europe with integrated battery and steering stop</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wide tires and 120mm suspension fork for off-road action</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pinion E1.12 Motor.Gearbox.Unit with Gates Carbon Drive belt</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Price (select model): €7,799</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://tout-terrain.de/en/the-products/e-bikes/e-x.over/divide/10940/divide?c=269\" target=\"_blank\"><em>tout-terrain.de</em></a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/tout-terrain-divide-emtb-pinion-motor-gearbox-unit/\">Tout Terrain Introduces Divide eMTB with Pinion Motor.Gearbox.Unit</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"69f1206702f6e393b9f1aa0766e8b090994d071c528bfd4bd53619134bacdf9e","category":"Cycling"}